reviews: No idea how this is a 3 star hotel as it absolutely should not be. Really strongly recommend NOT staying here. The only positive thing to say is it was good motivation to not want to be in our room. It was really dirty with mold covered bathroom and walls, weird smells, paper thin walls, flickering lights, dirty carpets, and an overall bad feel to the place as a whole. Many better comparable options in the area such as Hotel Oratio which is fantastic. Seriously one of the worst hotels I’ve stayed at.

We were guests at the hotel for 4 nights in early May, 2023. The hotel is very conveniently located near many attractions (Musée de Cluny, Panthéon, Arènes de Lutèce) and restaurants in the 5th arrondissement. Front desk personnel were very welcoming and cheerful and did not hesitate to provide us with any assistance we requested. Our hotel room was neatly cleaned and refreshed every day and the breakfast buffet was excellent! Nicole did an excellent job of keeping the breakfast area clean and ready to accommodate the customers as well as ensuring the buffet items were restocked. Thanks to all hotel staff for a job well done.

Hotel was conveniently located and in walking distance of many attractions. Desk staff were friendly and extremely helpful, especially Marie. She attended to our every need. Rooms were small but we did not really stay in them except to sleep. Will come back if I’m in Paris again.

It was an awesome birthday stay. We stayed in the room 27 with a 70's vibe and I liked it. The room was very spacious. The staff are friendly and welcoming specially we were greeted by my kababayan Lizabel. I would totally recommend this hotel.

Receptionists were very helpful and kind, always with a smile on their face. 5 star for that. Breakfast area was always clean and bfast was great too.
However, bathroom tiles and cubicle weren't so clean. Thin walls between rooms.

From my first contact with the hotel over the internet the hotel answered all my questions efficiently and while we arrived very early in the morning they happily looked after our bags, allowed us to wait in their lounge, use their Wi-Fi and then organised an early check in for a very reasonable price.
The room was reached by elevator and although small served our purposes with a separate bathroom, toilet and room for our luggage. `The bed was very comfortable and the room had a small balcony with a nice view of typically Parisian street below. We only booked two nights as we are travelling but we’re impressed enough to book several more nights next month.
The reception staff couldn’t have been more helpful and friendly. Melanie great with advice and booked our taxi to the train station. She, and the night staff and breakfast people made our stay very easy and comfortable.

My husband and I stayed at this hotel for a number of nights in the second half of March this year. It was the first time we had been there, and this was because our regular hotel on the same street was being renovated.
The hotel staff are very friendly and helpful, and the buffet continental breakfast was nicely displayed and with plenty of choices. Tea and coffee and a piece of pastry were available in the afternoons in the reception area. I am not aware whether this is normal procedure or not but was very welcome.
Our room needed some TLC (part of the curtain hanging off the rail and fabric coverings very worn), plus the cleaning could have been more effective. We had the feeling that the hotel was being renovated with work going on, on another floor which could account for some of our impressions. Our bathroom was a good size with ditto shower cubicle and plenty of hot water.
The room had a small fridge which was definitely a plus. There was also a good size safe box – big enough to put a laptop.
The hotel is situated very close to the Panthéon monument and approx. 10 mins walk from the Notre-Dame Cathedral and approx. 15-20 mins from the very impressive Hotel de Ville (the town hall). The beautiful Luxembourg Gardens are very close by.
My evaluation of the hotel is between 3 and 4, but because some of the criticism could be due to ongoing renovation work, I have chosen 4.

A three minute walk from the Metro (Line 10 Maubert) so we found it really easy to access all the main attractions with 30 mins door to door being the max.

Hotel staff were extremely friendly, professional and helpful.

Continental breakfast was quite varied and enjoyable in an extremely modern and clean setting.

We thought that the price we paid was very reasonable for the location with all the attractions accessible so quickly on the metro.

A few little niggles.

Walls are paper thin and you can clearly hear the neighbours talking.

Only one mirror in the room so a bit of a pain for two people to get ready at the same time.

Curtain between bedroom and toilet so make sure you're really, really toilet comfortable with the person you're staying with!

Room was nice and clean but a lot more basic than the rooms that are shown on the website.

The few little niggles wouldn't stop us staying again, we would just ask for a better room (we were in room 42).

We stayed here whilst visiting Paris for the rugby. Friendly staff, super clean rooms, comfortable bed. Very close to Notre Dame and good public transport links. All in all a very pleasant stay. When we visit Paris we would definitely stay again.

Spent 4 nights at this hotel with my family. The staff are very friendly, and speak fluent english. The room was clean, good central heating with also an aircondition installed. Bathroom is quite big. Breakfast was ok. Only a few metres from bars, restaurants, underground, buses etc. Price was moderate when we made the booking.

First of all, the location is great, ten+ minutes to Notre Dame and other places one likes to see, good restaurants nearby, very friendly staff, rooms are by no means big, but who comes to Paris to stay longer than needed in your room? The cleaning lady could use either a raise or an intro to better clean the floor (otherwise it was clean and neat) , breakfast is plenty and good, for 3 stars it's great.

I did not get to stay at the hotel so will only review the customer service. The hotel cancelled my reservation claiming that the credit card I had booked with is invalid. This is not true. I only have one card that I use almost daily and it works very well which was also confirmed by my bank when I called them.
I informed the hotel about this but they insisted that my card is invalid and cancelled my booking in stead of trying to find a solution since it must be a problem at their end as I have today used it without any problems both in a store and online and the hotel I stayed with last week had no issues with the same card.

Bit dated and worn, but the location is unbeatable and it was clean and comfortable. Check-in was very friendly and efficient. No problems with noise either from outside (and we faced the main street) or within as mentioned in some other reviews, but also it was during the week in January, so perhaps a bit more quiet than usual. Very good value for money. Would definitely stay again.

I think my expectations were quite high considering the good reviews, the pictures on the website which was very in keeping with our usual taste and the cost in comparison to other good quality Paris hotels.

Pros:
Staff - I genuinely can't fault the staff they were absolutely lovely. From the staff on front desk to the maids they were so nice.
Location - this location is perfect for exploring Paris. There are plenty of restaurants near by, you're close to tram routes and the Louvre, Notre dame and the Parthenon are all walking distance.
Beds - the bed was comfortable
Shower - water pressure was good and I loved the rain shower.

Cons:
Cleanliness - I'm not going to lie I wanted to scrub the room. The skirtings were filthy and there was dirt in the corners of the floors.
Black mould: like other reviews I agree about the mould in the bathroom. There was mould in the shower, where you hung your towels and in the grouting of the shower divider and around the window.
Size of room - Paris hotel rooms are small - this was a new level 🤣
Noise - the walls are thin. This meant that we hear guests coming and going through the night and next door were clearly smoking in the room because it was coming through the walls.

Did we complain? No because we wanted a stress free weekend and it's not something we would do. On the whole I'd say if you're going to explore Paris and are wanting somewhere comfortable to put your head at night it's perfect. If you are looking for a romantic break somewhere nice then it's not the place to go. It was okay but we wouldn't come back.

One of the best 3* hotels we stayed in. Air conditioning worked perfectly, the room was spacious, hotel’s staff was competent and friendly. Special thanks to Marie!

Sleep quality was very good, too. Our windows were facing a quiet street.
We would not hesitate to book the hotel again.

We have stayed at The Hotel Moderne twice since 2019. We keep coming back because we like everything about this hotel. It is very clean, comfortable, reasonably priced, has wonderful front desk staff, and is in a superb location. The area is just down the street from the Pantheon, up from Blvd. Saint Germain and near Notre Dame with many very good bistros on the block and a lively student energy from the nearby schools giving the ancient area fa timeless energy. The hotel rooms are very lively in varied colors and wallpaper patterns and have good lighting with some creative aspects including different colors if desired. The rooms are very clean, the beds are comfortable, the wifi and TV are great, the bathrooms very clean and stylish with strong water pressure and a towel heater on the wall. We really appreciated as well the abundance of electric outlets in the room for charging phones and camera a laptop, etc. Both times we had the Superior Twin room at the end of a hall on the front of the hotel and the rooms were quiet. This is a non-smoking hotel. They stayed open during all of the pandemic and are very alert to all Covid issues and have a plexiglass panel in front of the reception desk. All of the front desk staff speak several languages including English, and in particular I very much appreciated Marie, Anaide, and Rudy, all of whom were exceptionally friendly and very helpful. They have a nice breakfast for only 8 Euros and they have coffee, tea and cold drinks available all day. When you leave the hotel they will ask you to give your key to the front desk and they will give it to you when they return; there is someone at that reception desk 24/7. So no worries there. The air conditioning is excellent which was much appreciated in the mid-June heat. Metro stops are within two blocks, and taxis and buses are right outside the hotel easily available. There are markets and shops all around and anything you need you can easily find. Also lots of bookstores in this literary neighborhood. This is a hotel we will keep coming back to in Paris and I look forward to doing so again.

I hate to say I was a bit disappointed by our stay. It wasn't terrible by any means; I think I just had high expectations based on the very high score on here and on Google. It could just be that we were in the worst room in hotel (based on everyone else raving about their rooms!). I'd recommend against room 12 if you can help it.

The pros:
-The day staff at the desk downstairs were very friendly- always greeted us when we came and left.
-The location was very close to the metro and to a train to get to/from the airport. It was about an hour walk to the Eiffel Tower.
-There was a 24 hour desk, which was good since we arrived very late due to a delayed flight. The night clerk didn't seem thrilled to have to deal with our check-in, but he was helpful enough.
-Bed was comfortable
-Water pressure was great in the shower
-Towel heater in the bathroom was very effective and managed to dry all our clothes after we were soaked to the bone in an expected thunderstorm.

The cons:
-The mold in the shower was my number 1 complaint. I don't ask for a lot in a hotel- mainly a clean bed and a clean shower, but the mold on the shower floor right where we stood grossed me out. I did mention it to the front desk when we checked out. The hotel was full while we were there, so I didn't bring it up earlier since it wasn't something that could be fixed immediately and there wasn't another room to move us to. There was also mold on the wall grout where we hung our towels. Maybe this isn't a major issue for others though.
-The breakfast room was a bit small and was packed every day when we went down. We ended up just grabbing a croissant in a napkin to bring back up to the room. There are lots of bakeries nearby that are a much better option- just wish we hadn't paid for the breakfast.
-There wasn't a Do Not Disturb sign, so the cleaning staffed knocked on the door each morning and came in regardless of whether we need anything that day. We would've preferred someone not come into the room each day when we were out.
-The hairdryer worked for 11 seconds before needing a break to cool off. I mentioned it to the front desk, who said this was an intentional safety feature. They did say there was a hairdryer at the front desk that I could come down and borrow each day, but that felt like a hassle. Instead I'd dry my hair in 11 second spurts-- give it 2-3 mins to cool off, 11 more seconds...get fed up and decide damp was good enough. The hairdryer could only be used on the hottest setting, so there wasn't an option to just use it on a lower/cooler setting. If you do find yourself in this boat, after it shuts off, wait til you hear it click and then it's ready for another 11 seconds of use. Sometimes you might get a whole 15 seconds.

We loved our stay in a superior double room with a balcony. The staff were sweet, location was great with short walking distance to everything. We didn’t have breakfast at the hotel, we bought pastries and baguettes at a nearby boulangerie which was really nice. We will definitely stay here again.

We had a great time at the hotel Moderne Saint Germain.
Breakfast was great and the rooms were comfortable.
The staff was very professional . Especially Anaide who was very attentive to our needs.
We will come back to see the team with our friends !!!
Thank you!!!!

The hotel is very well located, in a short walking distance to the Panteon.
The staff is very helpful, especially Marie, who would always help us with a smile on her face whenever we needed assistance (same goes for the other staff members, who were always very friendly and helpful)!
The only 3 things that don´t let me give this hotel a 5-star rating are:
- The room which is too small and doesn´t even have a closet.
- The shower was very small in the bathroom and it was not that easy to take a shower without hitting the arms or legs.
- The food served for breakfast could be better. Even the croissants were not that good.

I enjoyed so much this hotel, the staff is so helpful and friendly, especially Marie. The breakfast is tasty, the room are colourful, amazing view from the fifth floor. The location is central. I'll definitely return it's very recommended.

Our travel agent booked this hotel for us and so happy that he did! Location was great (metro just 2 blocks away). Our room was perfect with a little balcony on the 5th floor. The bed was soft and big for my 6'3 ft husband and they have air condition which is great. Rooms are clean and housekeeping does a great job. I initially thought leaving the room key at the front desk was a little weird, but actually realized the benefit of not losing your key which was actually super nice not to have to worry about. The only thing I was not a fan of (and noticed this in other places so may be just a cultural difference) is that the heater was on in the breakfast area when it was 20 C( 70F) outside so it made it a little too warm for us, but the breakfast server was great.

Would also high recommend going to La Petite Périgourdine which is on the same block for dinner (great service and food) as well as Maison FOREST on the same street for coffee/pastries. The pastries were so good.

Special shout out to Marie. She was the first person we met and she was great. She laid everything out and gave us some really good food recommendations and made us feel super welcomed. She was also the person that checked us out and let us know about the benefit of the room we had as we had one of the larger rooms in the hotel. Which is super good to know for next time. Room 57 if you're interested. It's super big for a Paris hotel!

My boyfriend and I stayed for one night (4/27) at this hotel before departing for our flight home the next day. When we checked in we took some things out, including my boyfriend’s laptop which he uses for work. It stayed in the room the entire time. After watching a show on it in the evening, I placed it under the bed, so not to step on it, on the right side, barely sticking out.

In the morning, we regrettably forgot to pack it and only realized we had left it in the hotel room when we arrived at the airport. Upset with having forgotten it, we were hopeful the hotel could hold it for us and could arrange to ship it. After calling to ask to check for it in our room, 26, the front desk clerk Marie, informed us it was not there. Confused, my boyfriend asked them to check the entire room, move the bed over etc. Quite frankly, it would be hard to miss seeing a 14 inch-sized silver hp laptop under the bed.

After a bit of back and forth calls from the airport, another woman from the hotel simply told my boyfriend they went to look through the room with the maid and didn’t find anything. The laptop has a GPS tracker (the battery is now dead) which showed that it was still at the hotel…

My boyfriend and I are very upset and confused at how his laptop has just “disappeared” and would like to further investigate with management. An otherwise nice stay at this hotel has turned our experience sour after this ordeal.

We stayed at the hotel for a week and we had a great time. When we looked for recommendations for restaurants, Anna helped us and gave us realy good recommendations. The rooms were very clean and the location of the hotel was very good and near everything.

It’s a solid three star. Clean rooms and pleasant staff. Excellent location. Minutes from Notre Dame cathedral in the Latin Quarter. I’d stay there again. Close to metro and bus lines. Noisy on 3rd floor with windows open but when closed the windows are great at blocking sound.

Perfectly located in the Latin quarter, 5-minute walk to the metro station
Nearby, there are some good restaurants and cafè.

The double room with balcony was perfect: simple with a nice design and clean.
Same thing for the bathroom, with a big shower box.
In addition the staff was friendly.

For its price, it was a big deal.

Friendly staff, fun decor and excellent room. For a hotel in such a great location this was very reasonably priced at 99€ for a very comfortable twin room with balcony overlooking the lovely Rue des Ecoles in the Latin Quarter of Paris.
Despite being in the centre of the city, it was very quiet at night. Thank you!

Annual trip to Paris stayed at this hotel over 10 times now and always had a lovely time.Location great for getting around all Paris has to offer and plenty of nice restaurants nearby.Reception staff really helpful and friendly especially the lady (sorry didn’t get your name) who fixed the television in our room.Hopefully will be back again next year.

I hate writing a bad review, but while this hotel is in a great location and the staff is very friendly, the rooms weren't great. Aside from the very funky and velvety walls (which I can definitely overlook), there was a lot of black mold in the bathroom. There is no ventilation in the bathroom and the mold is pretty prevalent. So much so that I started to get sick from it. The room itself is a bit dingy and the A/C stopped working as well. Overall, I wouldn't stay here again.

I loved this place! Perfectly located, amazing staff (reception people were so kind and supportive!), funky rooms. I got one on the 6th floor, with a small balcony and great view on the street. Note, street can get noisy in the night/early morning but with the windows closed I could hear nothing. Also, one weird thing was lack of bathroom door in my room but I think it was part of the concept, my mother in law had a room on the 5th floor and there was a door present. We haven't tried the breakfast so can't judge it, instead we went to the Jozi Cafe and I can highly recommend it. As for Moderne, definitely a place to come back to.

The cleaning lady or someone of the staff stole our stuff from our room. They were rude and they didn't care. It's outrageous!
Everything about the hotel was a big disappointment. The rooms are small, noisy and smelly. The corridors and the elevator were dirty. The breakfast was poor and the same every day. It is like a bad dormitory. Disgusting!

Good central location. Rooms a bit small but well equipped and clean. Great air-conditioning during warm september weather. Staff very helpful and friendly. Staff operating in difficult conditions to get back to normal. Would use this again if we are back in this area.

Excellent location. Very comfortable room-excellent lighting, multi channel wall mounted flat screen tv, shower was a good size. Wi fi was excellent. Very friendly, welcoming and helpful staff! The continental breakfast was excellent- whole wheat roll. plain roll, croissant, pain au chocolate, a pastry, great orange juice ,coffee and tea. Very nice breakfast room. Many restaurants close by for dinner.

Awesome! We stay for 3 days and was wonderful.
Thanks also to the receptionist Marie that s do our trip stay so wonderful!
Totally recommended.
Clean , tidy and so quite …modern and actual hotel to stay in Paris
Perfect location and perfect to stay with the Family

This was our second stay (5 nights) in two years. It's a very comfortable hotel with a modern vibe in an absolutely superb location. We liked the cool decor.

The nice, fluffy slippers that used to await you in your room after check-in are gone now, and the water glasses have been replaced by plastic ones. Also, no more all-day espresso and croissants that used to be available in the downstairs lounge - gone, probably due to Covid. Still, we were happy there, especially in our 6th floor room that had a tiny terrace with a nice view. All the rooms are small but have plenty of storage space..

One negative: the rooms are frequently not cleaned until later afternoon/early evening which makes coming home for a break in the afternoon, especially on a hot day, to take a shower, change and relax before heading out again a bit problematic.

Would stay there again.

One of my favorite hotels now in Paris -- I just decided. Nice hotel, fabulous personnel, fabulous smiles, very helpful and friendly. My stay was short -- too short -- but very nice and the Hotel Moderne Saint Germain was a great last minute find. I will be back

My stay at Hotel Modern was just wonderful.

Hotel staff were very professional, upgraded me to a balcony room with a great view of paris. Room was quiet at night, super lively in the morning.

Hotel location is great for finding cafe's and bakery's all around the hood.

conclusion, even if it's Covid, you should go to paris, and this hotel is super well accommodating.

The hotel is so good and so nice! Room 32 with the Saint Germain graffitti is a must! The staff is very helpful, particularly Kosky. Also great location, just a few minutes from Notre Dame. I love it!

I never thought I could stay over 3 months in the same hotel, but I was in Paris during the COVID crisis, and was lucky to book Hotel Le M Saint Germain, since it was one of the few hotels that continued to remain open.

The first things I noticed was the chic and modern style of the hotel, and how each room has a different theme. I spent my first few weeks in a red room on the 3rd floor, and I absolutely loved it. My favorite part of the room was the huge bathroom.

On my third month, the staff upgraded me to a double room with a balcony on the 6th floor. It was bright, and had a fantastic view of the 6th floor, I quickly made this room my home.

The place is very tidy, and staff are always so accommodating and friendly, and they treated me like family. I especially enjoyed the chats getting to know the team (Marie, Anaide, Rudy & Krosky at the reception), as well as Nicole, the extra friendly lady who would tidy the rooms.
The hotel location (5th arrondissement, few minutes away from Notre Dame) and with great metro access was a huge relief.

I felt so at home at this hotel, that every time I come to Paris in the future, I will make sure I stay here. I definitely recommend.

This hotel’s convenient location is unbeatable! It was our first time in Paris and it was easy for us to get to all the must-see attractions. The Quartier Latin is a charming and safe area.

The hotel seems to be newly refurbished. We loved how cosy and stylish our room was! I guess every room has a different layout and this uniqueness made our stay special.

Breakfast area is equally modern and breakfast is awesome.

We will be back!

I have never been so disappointed with any service provider. We were forced to leave the hotel because of the US stopping domestic flights and France closing their borders. We had three nights including breakfast left and management won’t even give us a credit to use in November of this year. I REFUSE to stay here again because of this horrible customer service beyond anyone’s control.

Had they given us a credit I would have happily started here again despite the very small rooms, lack of hot water in the evenings, and mediocre breakfast. The staff was friendly but I cannot tolerate or stomach such greed - take your money elsewhere.

We stayed here in Mid February and found this hotel to be darling! We love the location, very close to metro and RER. Plenty of places to eat a good dinner, coffee, pastries and near plenty of little grocery stores for snacks. We stayed in the St Germain de Pres Room and it was adorable! We loved the views and city noise ( it wasn't excessive, but if you like a quieter room, they may be able to accommodate )
Everyone employee we encountered at the hotel was friendly and helpful. Everyone spoke 3 languages, quite impressive!
We would stay here again and recommend this place to family + friends!
Thank you so much Hotel Le M for a wonderful stay!

Absolutely nothing bad to say about this hotel!! Location is great if you’re coming to visit and walk around Paris, the rooms are very nice, comfortable and clean. Service is impeccable and the french breakfast is very tasty, the bread is just to die for!
Would totally recommend this hotel for either solo travelers as well as couples or families!

Don’t go to this hotel!!
This hotel treats guests like trash!! They are the worst hosts ever!! Never in my life I saw such lack of cordially!! I have no words to describe the arrogance of the staff!! It’s unreal really!! WORST HOTEL EVER!!!

Nice, modern accommodation. Anaïde of front desk staff was very helpful. Room was big and comfortable. Overall handy location, Louvre and Notre Dame in walking distance, as is metro and bus lines. We were on 6th floor and there are lofts only from ground to level 5. We had to carry heavy suitcases up to our level. Shower was open and there way no way to close anything off/have privacy. Otherwise, this hotel is great accomodation in Paris.

Hotel is well located in the latin quarter. Checkin was nice and easy and the girl on reception was very friendly and accommodating, but otherwise the service was generally lacking.
Emailed the hotel 5 days prior to arriving and only got a response 1 day prior to arriving.
Guys on reception generally sounding unfriendly and like any question was interrupting them.
Rooms were very small but that's not uncommon for Paris and for the price. Shower was a bit annoying as it didn't have a proper door and got the room wet quite often.
Breakfast was fine, continental style

I went to paris from Nov 21st to Nov 27th, and stayed at Le M Saint Germain, after a lot of research and almost booking with a Mercure one. And I must say, I could not be happier that I chose them.

Upon arrival, on a rainy wednesday afternoon, I was received by Marie at the reception, who took care of my check in, giving my advices and tips to get around Paris, as well as explaining rules and functioning of the hotel itself. Kindly, I was informed that the room I could not have been given the room I had asked due to different categories, but that I was put into the most similar one corresponding to my category.

Proceeding to my room on the 2nd floor, I took the elevator, which is fairly small (3 to 4 people, no bags, is the maximum it can handle). Room 24 is in front of the elevator, and is pretty straightforward: a double bed, a desk with a chair and minibar, a closet, window with balcony, A/C, heater and wall-mounted TV. As for the bathroom, bear in mind you are in Europe, and especially in Paris, so space is not really a plus (except you're willing to pay 400€ /day). A shower, toilet, sink with blow dryer and rack to hand towels, all the essential. A kit with shampoo, body gel and body moisturizer is also available and refilled when needed.

The variety in the breakfast is not so big, but you have a coffee machine with many options to choose from, a minibar with plenty of yogurt available, 4 to 5 types of fresh fruit juice, croissants, pain au chocolat, 2-3 types of bread, cold cuts, hazelnut spread, butter and fruits available. All is refilled before you can notice.

The vibe of the hotel is very nice: modern (as its name says), vibrant, happy, exciting.
The surroundings are very nice: you have a metro station a block away from the hotel (Maubert-Mutualité, from line 10), and while you walk from it to the hotel, you can spot the Panthéon at the end of the street - a very gorgeous view! Literally next to the hotel, there is a pizza place (Pizza Roma Écoles) with amazing authentic italian pizzas and pasta. Boulangeries and patisseries are also around, as well as bistros. A great, great plus is having a Franprix on the same block, which is no more than a 3-minute walk to.

All in all, my staying there was perfect! Staff is very friendly (props to Marie and the night guy, that I was not able to get the name, for being so nice to me) and ready to help with whatever you need. I will definitely stay there again, and recommend this hotel for anyone who wishes to have the most pleasant stay in Paris!

I have been to many hotels in Paris (see my other reviews over the years), so I have a pretty reasonable understanding of what to expect. The location is outstanding. I have previously stayed in this area---right next door at the Hotel Saint Jacques, in fact. This was my first stay at this hotel.
I booked this hotel for my sister and myself (two single rooms) on Expedia with breakfast included.
We arrived very early in the day so our rooms were not ready. We went out and about while the hotel locked our luggage in a secure room.
Upon return at around 3pm, our rooms were ready. The staff were very pleasant. When I went into my room, it was fine. Nothing spectacular, nothing ornate. The room was very basic--a bed, a closet with shelves, and a desk with a chair. It was not huge, but it was comfortable for one person. There were nice, large French doors that opened onto the rue des Ecoles below. I enjoyed opening the windows to hear and see Paris!

The Bathroom
There is no actual door to the bathroom, just a very heavy curtain. This was fine as I was in my room alone and privacy was not an issue. I do have to say, that my only concern was in the bathroom. I am a relatively small person (5'5" and not overweight) and the shower was SMALL. I could not shave my legs because I could not lift my leg and shave it--and I could not bend entirely over to reach my leg without my head hitting the wall. When washing my hair, I had to keep my elbows somewhat down or they hit the walls of the shower. If my husband or sons had been on this trip and needed to use this type of shower, it would have been impossible as they are tall with athletic builds (6'4" and muscular)--they would not have fit in the shower. It worked okay for me, but it was tight.
I had only one complaint, which I voiced to the reception personnel. There was a significant amount of black mold in my shower. I asked the personnel on day 1 if they could put some bleach or something on the mold to remove it. I am sensitive to mold, and it is just not safe especially in a very small shower and being fueled by hot shower water. The mold was never addressed,and I just tried to take a very fast shower to avoid inhaling any potentially airborne mold.
Breakfast
The breakfast area was pleasant and the food was a very typical French fare. I was a bit disappointed that there were no actual baguettes there, instead rolls and other breads. There were croissants, fruit, yogurt, deli meats and wonderful cheese. The coffee machine was great as well.
The Lobby
The lobby area is a bit small, but it serves its purpose. There is hot tea, coffee and some small croissants and pain au chocolat available in the afternoon, which was a nice touch.

Overall, it was a fine stay, but if I go back to this area, I would probably not stay at this hotel again. The area is great though--very safe, even at night. The hotel location is really wonderful and the staff were very pleasant.

It's a typical Paris hotel with small rooms, but it has A/C and the nicest, most helpful staff we have ever met! It is within an easy walk to a metro stop. And in good location for other sites within walking distance. They even stored our bags for us after check out because our train didn't leave for a few hours. We would definitely stay here again!

My husband and I, along with his parents, stayed here in mid October. The location is great, centrally located in the Latin Quarter, very close to Notre Dame, and easy walking to many attractions. Yes, the rooms are small but for location, this is a perfectly acceptable amount of space. My husband and our three LARGE bags had no issues. If you’re expecting a large hotel room, try paying 1000€ a night!

I’m reviewing this hotel mostly for the FANTASTIC service of the front desk staff. Marie, Ariane, and the others went beyond any expectations to make sure we were comfortable, ordered taxis, confirmed “local” not tourist prices, and more. I know Americans expect French people, and particularly Parisians, to be rude but I was so incredibly pleased with the staff at Hotel Le M and Parisians as well!

I've been to Europe before and knew that rooms are small there, but the room in this hotel was a bit bigger than a broom closet. I arrived there before 11:00 am because I had just come from the airport from an overnight flight. I knew I would not be able to check in until later, but I just wanted to have my suitcase put in a storage closet until later in the day when I would be allowed to check in. You would have thought I asked for a million bucks. The desk clerk was sarcastic and rude. He did put the bags in a closet finally but then I got a lecture about "showing up early." After checking in, I was told that any time I left the hotel I had to leave my key at the front desk. That was annoying. On the positive side, the hotel is in a great location in the Latin Quarter neat the beautiful Luxembourg Gardens and the Sorbonne. Breakfast there was $20.00 and was basically cereal, juice and coffee. I didn't eat it there. There is a coffee machine in the room. The hotel is near a Metro station. I only stayed one night, so it was good enough for my brief stay. Showers were sort of half open, so you have to be careful or water will get on the floor.

My wife and I had visited Paris on 5 previous occasions and on this occasion we decided to find a new location. The cost of the room was a bit more expensive than past visits but we were happy to book based on the hotel location and photos displayed on the hotels own web site.

Unfortunately the only part of our stay we enjoyed was the hotels location.

Upon initial arrival we were taken by surprise to see that the exterior of the hotel bore no resemblance to the photo displayed on their own web site.

The second and most disappointing aspect was the size of the room. It was so small that we found it most uncomfortable.

Once again the room we thought we book based on the web site photo was way smaller than the impression given via the web site.
Being experienced travellers we initially considered booking out early but in the end we just decided to spend as much time as possible out of the hotel.

Every time we returned to our room we felt a high degree of disappointment and honestly believe that the hotel does misrepresent itself on its web site.

On the positive side we felt the staff were very pleasant.

Small hotel in the Latin Quarter. A good location for restaurants, and close to the metro. Reception staff were very helpful. Breakfast was adequate, although might get a bit boring after a few days. Excellent coffee machine, but disappointed with the croissants which were small, not particularly crispy, and not really what I would expect in Paris!
Our room was a bit disappointing, it had everything you might need, but it was small. We expected more for what we had paid. But then again, this is Paris! We concluded that there were simply too many bedrooms in this relatively small building. Result: tiny rooms. There was little room around the bed. The shower was good, although bathroom floor got quite drenched due to an open entrance to the shower.
We were not impressed with room cleaning simply because it was not usually done until late in the afternoon, even though we would have gone out fairly early. We returned one day to relax a bit but found room not made up, so we were asked to go and wait downstairs!
As previously mentioned, please note that you will receive one room key only, which must be left at reception when you go out, which is a bit of a pain!

Nice hotel in great location. Very clean. Wonderful staff! They are all very helpful, but I would like to specially thank Marie and Michael. They did a big extra effort and help me as translators when I met my french family. A big thank you for both of them!

This was our third short visit to Paris this year for opera. We stayed near the Marais on the two previous occasions and didn't wish to return to either hotel. This time we paid much more money and, apart from the hotel being in a more touristy area, we didn't feel that the extra expense was worth it.
We arrived at about 6.0 pm. As we walked into the lobby, the strong smell of tobacco smoke hit us and the guy on reception couldn't have been less welcoming if he'd tried.
Our room (a superior double - what does an ordinary double look like I wonder?) was small with one hard chair and a padded stool. The shower in the bathroom isn't closed in, so the floor gets soaked.
On our third day, we went out at 10 am and returned at 5.0 pm to find that the room still hadn't been serviced. Having to hand n the room key each time we went out meant that when we returned late one evening we had a long wait while the guy behind the desk dealt with two women in front of us.
Breakfast was fine, but I would have liked fresher croissants and freshly baked baguettes.
The two women who were sometimes on the front desk were so much more welcoming and friendly than the men.

We received a lovely welcome to le M and the room/property was a reasonable 3 star option. A couple of staff at reception were a bit ordinary. Small but comfy room and the location was good. For us, it was very expensive for what it was, but that's Paris :)

This hotel is in a great location and I had high hopes based on other reviews. We cannot sleep or enjoy our stay here because the a/c is broken in our room and it is very hot i(we are on the 6th floor). . We specifically only booked hotels that had air conditioning as it is very warm here, so we are not receiving the value we paid for and we are too uncomfortable to sleep. The front desk staff was not apologetic at all and basically told us there was nothing they could do. Would definitely not recommend this hotel as there are many others that are in a good location AND care about the comfort of their guests!

Stayed in this hotel at the end of August for several nights. Found the location good, being in a less touristy area near the Pantheon but pretty close to Notre Dame, metro, bus and bars, cafes and ammenities.
Front desk service was always nice and courteous. There were 2 things that I was disappointed about.
One day I returned to find the room door open - it was disconcerting. My room door didn’t close itself (needed to be pushed closed) so assumed the cleaner may have forgot to push it close after they finished. Nothing was missing and valuables were in safe so guess it was just a mistake. One of my friends’ rooms also had a door that didn’t close itself (weak door mechanism?). I informed the front desk and they were apologetic.
The second thing was the room was extremely noisy. I was near the lift so that didn’t help but even when I was in the hallway I could hear people at the end of the hallway talking in their room clearly and loudly, even though their door was closed. I had a lot of issues sleeping in, even with ear plugs. I explained this to the front desk and they said that it is an older building. I’ve been in a bunch of old hotels, including Paris and I’ve never had this much of a problem with noise and suspect adding carpet in rooms and thicker carpet in hallways might help.
Anyway, I liked the location and the staff but was disappointed with these 2 things.

We found the Hotel to be pleasant and welcoming. We had a superior room which was small which you would expect in a City Hotel, very clean, nicely decorated and suited our needs perfectly. Breakfast room was bright and modern with a good selection for a continental breakfast. Drinks and snacks available in the afternoon for guests. All staff were very polite and helpful. Happily stay there again. :-)
Our suggestion would be to put closers on doors and signs asking people to shut doors quietly.

Myself and my husband stayed for 2 nights and found the hotel to be modern however our room was really small and we had a curtain for the toilet door. The hotel area was lovely and was very central. The staff were all lovely and the hotel was very clean.

Once again, thanks to Trip Advisor, we found this lovely Paris Hotel. Everything was perfect--starting with the fact that the rooms were air conditioned--when we arrived during a horrid heat wave. We very much appreciated the lift--as many small Paris hotels do not have lifts. The breakfast selection was excellent. There were more than enough healthy choices (as well as lovely breads), The best part was the staff--always friendly and helpful. As special shout-out to Marie, Anaiole, Issa and Rudy. If I left anyone out, so sorry--as all were wonderful.

And best of all, the location is perfect. Easy walk to the Metro as well as numerous restaurants and cafes. We have stayed in many locations in Paris--this was definitely the best hotel.

We really enjoyed our stay in this hotel. The rooms are modern and charming in its own way. The hotell staff are so friendly and polite and helpful with everything. Also a thumbs up for the great service by the cleaning staff. They did a really great job!
By the way, we will miss the big teddybear that was moved around the hotel :)

The hotel was located in a great area for walking about. Many restaurants and shops. We had a great experience with the staff and Mary at reception was amazing. She always had a smile, was extremely helpful and spoke perfect English. She was a true gem during our stay & made our experience great. Our room was on the top floor and served our needs. Air conditioning worked great and we had a little balcony. Rooms are quaint and very Parisian. Breakfast had pastries, cereal, fruit, cheese and meats - juices, coffee options - great for us.

I've been away many times and have never written reviews...but feel compelled to do so on this place.

Arrived in the evening to check-in. The room was ok, nice lighting, small but pleasant, no iron or board.

Went downstairs to go out about 12.30am, front door was locked wouldn't open on the push button...this is strange, concierge again nowhere to be seen, but came after a few minutes of calling out.....what if there was a fire!!!!

Came back at 3.30am, front door was locked......conciergre showed up after a few minutes of rining the bell.....wtf.....not great service!!!

Anyway i'm tired and go to bed, than at about 6.30am woke up to what felt like someone shining a bright ligt in my face....sunlight coming through the curtain....curtain was fully closed but couldn't reach one end so light beaming through
onto the pillows where my head is, had to take drastic action to block out the light. I see the management respond with some daft response so photos attached.

Told the concierge when checking out...apparently they would have put me in another room....like i'm gonna pack up all my stuff and wander down at 6.30am. wtf I want to sleep...how about a refund for putting me in a room not fit to be sold....!!!!!!!

Maybe I should contact the audit firm with the French Accreditation Committee.......

We stayed for 3 nights in a triple room. Found it really friendly, lovely staff, helpful including the hard-working women running breakfast. We found the breakfast buffet above expectation, with stacks of breads and pastries, cheeses and meats etc, real coffee machine. It was for us included, so a great way to fill up before sightseeing. Our triple room was bigger than expected from reviews and perfectly manageable in size. Bathroom was roomy with a really hot and powerful shower. The only negative comment is that the walls are thin and you can hear showers/water/doors a lot. But this always stopped at night in the end. The location us perfect. Off the main tourist area, feels safe and peaceful. Great access very nearby to Metros and Rer direct to CDG. No problem leaving baggage on last day. So we really loved it and would highly recommend.

The hotel is less than 2-star in American standard. Very small room, worn out/dirty carpet.

The staff was very unprofessional, even to the point of being rude. When there was issue to be resolved, they didn't offer any help.

We stayed here around Easter. The hotel is perfectly situated and within walking distance of the Notre-Dame. The receptionist (an American guy) was very welcoming upon arrival and gave us lots of information. I loved the style of the hotel. It was quirky and colourful. Room was very small but this is usual in Paris. Overall very good value for money.

My third time here, and i found it the same but better! Updated bathrooms and room decor are a plus; the shower was especially awesome, with instant hot water and forceful water pressure- both of which are hard to come by in this price range. My twin room was more spacious than any other Paris hotel I’ve stayed in. The front desk staff is stellar with ready smiles, great English and helpful in every way. The location is incredible, with a Metro a block away, tons of restaurants and also local cheese, wine, bread, pastries, and fresh fruits/ veggies every day and a market on Tuesday morning. Breakfast is basic but ample. I love this place!

Terrible, run down, we did not get the rooms shown in pics, we were stuffed in unsightly stalls, one without AC. In the end, as we were leaving, we were told by reception that next time we stay there (ha ha) they will give us good rooms. We should have called the police.

Small rooms but enough for a weekend in Paris. No complaints or feedback at all. Location is good, staff is good, rooms are good but small. You could easily hear sound from the hallway (elevator, talking, walking etc) but it was not very disturbing.

This is my absolutely favorite Paris neighborhood (Place Maubert), very central to everything, and surrounded by great food and wine stores and bistros and restaurants, and the wonderful weekend market just down the street.

The hotel has a very friendly and helpful staff and a very welcoming atmosphere. For instance, there is a nice downstairs lobby plus sitting/dining area where free coffee and pastries are provided afternoons into the evening.

The rooms (ours was a standard double) are quite small but the spaces are so cleverly designed that there is plenty of space for suitcases and all their contents. Super comfortable bed. Our bathroom and toilet were both ensuite but in separate spaces, which is great. The room had a coffee/tea maker and a mini fridge, enabling us to make our own breakfasts and chill some wine for the evenings. Nice toiletries, and even house slippers are provided. It seems like every room has a different contemporary design, very cool. Our room looked out on the street, with a classic Parisian view, but there were no noise issues whatsoever.

One note of caution: most rooms and bathrooms are definitely small, even the elevator barely accommodates two people and their luggage. Very large people may want to look elsewhere.

Definitely recommended.

We checked into the hotel for a nine day stay. The room we originally got had a very small bathroom with a tiny shower. We talked with the Front Desk staff - Mary and Anaide - and they were very helpful in reassigning us to a room that was much better. We really liked the location of the hotel, very convenient with easy access to Metro. Elevator was small but probably typical for Paris. All of the Front Desk staff were very friendly and helpful, and we were especially appreciative of the service we received from Mary and Anaide. They were both exceptional!

We stayed at this hotel for 3 nights and we liked it a lot. The staff was superfriendly and the rooms were nice and modern. It is situated in the 5th arrondissement near Sorbonne. This is a nice block and the bistrot ”L’Annexe” on the same street became a favourite!

Hotel le M is calm, relaxed and tidy. A perfect place for a few days' visit. Great service and the staff is truly friendly. The breakfast is surprisingly good, with fresh fruit salad and yoghurts, etc. Everything you need is here and the area is adorable. Thank you:) 1

Great little boutique hotel, location is perfect, close to Metro and Notre Dame Cathedral, restaurants. We had a nice clean room with French balcony, slept very well in comfortable beds. Good breakfast. The staff was wonderful and very helpful if needed. I would highly recommend staying here for location, nice and clean rooms, easy access, great staff.

Ebba and Peter Sweden

A comfortable little hotel in a great location. Check in was simple, staff helpful and a room on the 5th floor which had a small external balcony overlooking the main street. Bed was a nice size and comfortable, good TV, excellent heating and cooling and some basic mini bar items. Room also has a good sized safe and hanging space. Bathroom was a nice size for the room and good to use except for the shower design which meant water sprayed out all over the floor, very annoying. Breakfast buffet was good, a nice selection of items, all cold, and a good coffee machine.

This was a wonderful find. A beautiful boutique hotel, immaculately clean, extremely comfortable, wonderful staff, a great breakfast and it's location was brilliant! Would reccomend and use every visit

Absolutetly perfect.
Cosy small hotel in a perfect location.
Thanks to Mari for our stay.

Short walking distance to Notre Dame, Leuvre and other places in the Latin Quarter.
Staff in this hotel is very helpful

My mom, my sister and I had a wonderful stay in one of their triple rooms. The beds were very comfortable, it was a nice size and quiet at night despite being in a very central location. The staff was very friendly as well. Highly recommended for your stay in Paris!

I stayed during one week and everything was fine. Great staff, very polite and helpfull, specially Marie. The breakfast was good with fresh products. The room was clean and and exactly as shown in the photos. Thank you for everything.

Well located hotel for us as we like to stay in the fifth for the range of bars and restaurants on offer. For a Paris hotel the rooms are a bit more spacious than most with typically more room to manoeuvre in the bathroom. Also atypical for Paris there is a fridge and coffee/tea making facilities so we bring our own fresh milk and preferred tea bags etc so we can have breakfast biscuits and drinks in the room and save €25 or so each day. Breakfast in the hotel is OK but simple.

Last week the douaniers decided to work to rule at Gard du Nord specifically disrupting outgoing Eurostar and on the Thursday we were texted a message advising us not to travel the following day. So we were a bit stuck.

After a bit of research on the net we found the only sensible route home was to fly but nothing was available until the Saturday.

I went and spoke to the lady on reception who initially said they had no availability for the Friday night but offered to consult their sister hotel after a bit of discussion with her colleague she closed the call. And after a bit of keyboard work and clarification she said she had rearranged a few room allocations and freed up our existing room for the additional night. For which I was very grateful indeed - also the room rate was sensible - no attempt to rip off. So we were then able to book two of the last few remaining seats on the BA flight on the Saturday afternoon and relax and enjoy an extra day in the sunshine in Paris.

Thank you Hotel M - we will be back!!

Having travelled a bit of Europe for a few weeks this was my final stop in Paris. This hotel was the perfect place, the staff were amazing a helpful. The room was top notch amazing decor with mood lighting and comfy bed (much needed after my traveling). Breakfast was not included but it was a good price, with a selection of pastries and good coffee, I was very happy with it.
Only a short walk to Notre-Dame and river taxis to take you to the centre. Yet I still found my self walking along the river banks to get banks, just to see the city at night.
I would highly recommend this place to anyone wanting to visit Paris.

Great location. Little/No noise from the street. Good service from the staff. Room and bathroom are small-ish but well organized and comfortable . Simple breakfast but good. Fridge and safe in the room.

Great place to stay, staff are so helpful. Good location for everything. Great places to eat. Walking distance to river, then jump on the river bus.give this place a try very clean rooms good breakfast to set you up for the day

My name is Samirah Raheem, I am an model who traveled to Paris last minute to walk. Thank goodness Le M Saint Germain was able to accommodate me, especially because it can be so hard to find a hotel that is central around fashion week. Their staff was warm and welcoming and the location is perfect and made it so easy to get around the city. I was apprehensive about my stay because I've encountered rude staff in the past while staying in Paris, but the team really knows great customer service. Can't wait to come back!

PS: if you get lucky enough to be staying the same night as the receptionist, RUDY, he’s amazing and will go above and beyond for hotel guests. Extremely attentive, professional and mannered.

First, The location in my opinion is the best location in town.
In ten minutes walking you can see hundred of businesses, restaurants, supermarkets, public transportation, etc.
The hotel staff is really something to remember- all of them are very welcoming, helpful, and will help you with everything you need.
I want to say a good word for Issa from the reception, he really is a true professional and a nice guy, helped us and took care of our needs.
Oh, and the rooms are beautiful! :)

Well we stayed here in feb and had planned for 3 nites but decided to extend it for another 2 nites and it was Marie and anaide at the front desk who gave us the best deal. They both were really helpful with regards to guiding us. And finally the breakfast it was amazing and fresh n things were replinished quickly and all thanks to Nicole ....well all in all a wonderful stay and all thanks to d 3 ladies who had it wonderful

Our room was located on the 6th floor, but the lift only goes up to the 5th. It’s no biggie but thought that was weird. The room was clean, had a nice view of the city street below. Despite that, the noise was minimal. Location is great for exploring the left bank, just a few blocks from the Pantheon. However, the staff was not welcoming, though not rude...similar to a transaction at the post office. There are plenty of similar accommodations in Paris at this price point and standard so I’d look around some more if you want to be greeted by a warm staff as opposed to feeling like another transaction, especially while on vacation.

This is a great little boutique hotel on Rue de Ecoles. The University of Paris (Sorbonne) is about a block away. And the Notre Dame cathedral is less than a 10-minute walk. There are great dining and shopping options within minutes as well as the Pantheon up a hill just behind the hotel that has a pretty great nighttime view of the Eiffel Tower.

Rooms are not chain hotel standard, my sisters and I each had a single room and none of them were the same. Some items were standard, a small fridge, a wall-mounted television, and a small desk. My room was orange-ish, my sister on the fourth floor had a purple-ish room, and my sister on the third floor had a blue-ish room. Each of us had a small Juliet balcony that overlooked the street below. I took advantage of my fifth floor location and stood outside several times each day. I couldn't see much over the buildings nearby but they view was a terrific city scene.

One complaint, literally one, was there were not enough outlets in my room, I had to unplug either the fridge or the tea kettle to get a plug for my phone and table. But my sisters had plugs right next to their beds. Kind of a pain, but the plugs were easy to get to.

The staff was excellent, don't worry if your French is rusty or non-existent, they all speak English quite well and are super helpful. If you need to check in a bit early they can be accommodating, we arrived around noon and were allowed to check-in then. They can also arrange for transportation to the airport, about 90 euros for a van to CDG, which was about 30 euros less than we paid from the airport.

This was a terrific location, convenient to a lot of stuff and we loved it. They have wi-fi, a cute little lounge, and a nice breakfast area. HIGHLY recommended if you want something with a bit of character.

The staff were what made this hotel excellent. Everyone was friendly, helpful, and so welcoming! Location is perfect - close to the metro and restaurants but away from the very touristy areas. Room was a pretty good size for Paris. Cool design with nice storage area, safe, and large shower. The terrace was an awesome feature.

Great boutique hotel in the heart of the Latin Quarter - easy Metro access, wonderful markets close by, great walking neighborhood with many great restaurants within 5-10 minute walk. 5-10 minute walk to Notre Dame and Place St Michel as well. Standard (small) Paris sized rooms that have been updated. Plenty of space for two in the standard rooms, with decent sized bathroom facilities and quite large showers. Our room was on the back side of the hotel overlooking a nice "walk thru" alley. Super quiet on this side of the building. Some minor updating underway in the stairwell (painting) and possibly some new carpet being added. The staff was wonderful and super helpful if needed. Would highly recommend staying here for location, easy access, nice rooms, and great staff.

There were 8 adults in our party and from the start right through our stay the staff were excellent. Breakfast was well presented and plenty of choice. Rooms were very comfortable. Location superb for all the sightseeing whether walking or using the Metro.

The hotel is clean, the rooms have everything you need and the location is excellent. I also recommend the breakfast which has something for everyone.

However, the hotels greatest asset is its team who are very friendly and highly professional. On my last day in Paris, I managed to leave my handbag behind. We called the hotel from the Eurostar Terminal and asked if they would collect the bag from the restaurant where I left it and return it to me in the UK. They did so and I now have my bag back. Thank you so much!

I’ve just spent 2 nights at Hotel Moderne and it is a great place to stay in central Paris. Rooms are spotless (but a bit pokey) and you can walk to most places in central Paris (where I have been many times) while feeling you are in a neighbourhood.

The staff al speak English and are very friendly. For free you can leave your bags early and also leave them after you check out. Our room was on rue de Écoles but was still totally quiet. The breakfast was not cooked and a bit modest, but for €12 Euros it was worth it. Good luck!

Friendly staff, clean and funky decorated rooms. The rooms are comfortable even with three people in the triple room. The bathroom was clean and had a towel warmer. The staff was always great and willing to assist in any way. It is also in a great location.

I would recommend this hotel first and foremost as this is very close to a lot of local attractions in Paris including a 10 min walk to Notre Dame Cathedral and 3 minute walk to the nearest Metro service.
There are plenty of places to eat and drink locally along this stretch of road that the hotel is situated on and the staff here are very informative and very helpful in giving advice and directions to all local attractions.

The actual room itself was modern, (the neon light colour changer was a nice touch) but it was clean and had some amazing vibrant colours throughout and would suit any couple looking to stay on a budget, although I might add that this did have the appeal of a more mid range hotel.

We booked this hotel as it was within our budget and it seemed close enough to the sights we wanted to visit in Paris. It was also easy to get to from the metro stations (St.Michel-Notre Dame and Maubert-Mutualite). There were many restaurants around it that were well reviewed, plus a pharmacy just across the road for any emergency medical need. It was walking distance to the Notre-Dame Cathedral, as well as the Pantheon and the Luxembourg Palace / Park, as well as the Monge area where a popular pharmacy is for cosmetic shopping. Basically a very convenient location. The receptionists there were all very friendly and readily spoke very fluent English where needed. The room was rather small but it fitted our need. The deco was indeed very modern (reflecting the hotel name - Le Modern) - with soft blue hued lighting, with bedside lighting for reading. The TV was super HD and large - so settling in bed to just chill in with some entertainment was an added plus point. The bathroom, however we very small and only had a thick curtain as a door. So travellers who are shy about their toileting might want to ask for a room with a proper bathroom door if there's an option. The shower cubicle was very narrow, so if you're on the large side in terms of size, it'll be pretty difficult to maneuver in the shower without knocking into the sides of the cubicle. Otherwise, the room was very complete with coffee/tea-making facilities, a cupboard with a minibar-fridge and safe-deposit box. We had a room next to the main road and it was very quiet. There's airconditioning also. Breakfast is 8 euros per person if it's not part of the room package. Definitely recommended for a value-for-money stay with little frills.

Our travel agent picked this spot and we were very pleased with her choice.
The location is very good. Only two blocks from the Metro and a five minute walk to the pedestrian street off St.Germaine with tons of restaurants.
The reception staff are fluently bilingual, full of information, and very welcoming and helpful.
Our room was a bit small but probably equivalent to other hotels of similar rating. The bed was comfortable. There was plenty of storage space and an in-room safe.
The bathroom is tiny and has an odd curtain for a door, but otherwise is well equipped with fixtures, towels, and toiletries..
There was a nice balcony for watching the street.
Lots of TV channels but only new channels in English.
The Wifi worked well.
The continental breakfast was quite well. Not a ton of choices but everything provided was fresh and tasty. Great coffee machine.
I highly recommend and would revisit.

The location of the hotel is excellent! The receptionists are very nice and helpful with excellent English.
The breakfast area is very nice, but around 10.00 before the breakfast finishes it becomes crowded and difficult to serve yourself. When something finishes it takes a while to be replaced.
Art Deco style in the rooms. There wasn’t door to the bathroom, but very thick curtain. The room was very clean with tea amenities and toiletries.
At the moment there’s renovation of the staircase, which might be noisy in the morning after 8am.

A very nice place to stay in the Latin Quarter. Every room in the hotel has a different deco which makes every room special, the view over rue des Ecoles is so perfect you can smell the brad in the mornings and the wine in the afternoons. it's at walking distance from places like Notre Dame, the Pantheon, the Sorbonne, etc.
